PMID== 23954621
TI  == purification and characterisation of recombinant bacteroides fragilis toxin-2.
AB  == fragilysin (bft) is metalloprotease that is secreted by enterotoxigenic bacteroides fragilis. studying the mechanism of bft interaction with intestinal epithelial cells requires a pure protein sample. in this study, we cloned dna-fragments coding for the catalytic domain of fragilysin-2 and profragilysin-2 into an e. coli expression vector. purification methods for the recombinant fragilysin-2 catalytic domain and profragilysin-2 were developed. in addition, we obtained mature active fragilysin-2 from recombinant proprotein by limited tryptic digestion. we tested the biological activity of the recombinant protein samples and revealed that e-cadherin was cleaved when ht-29 cells were treated with mature fragilysin-2 but not with profragilysin-2. azocoll, azocasein and gelatin were not proteolytically cleaved by mature fragilysin-2. proteins released in culture medium after ht-29 cells treatment with mature active bft-2 were identified.
