TI  == [a reconstructed b. fragilis-derived recombinant alpha-galactosidase developed for human blood type b-->o conversion].
AB  == this study was aimed to prepare a reconstructed b. fragilis-derived recombinant alpha-galactosidase developed for human b to o blood group conversion. based on the construction of recombinant e. coli (de3) which can express alpha-galactosidase, the inducing time and inducer concentration were optimized for high expression of alpha-galactosidase. then, the expression products in supernatant were purified by cation and anion exchange column chromatography. the purified alpha-galactosidase was used to treat b group red blood cells in phosphate buffer (ph 6.8) for 2 hours to prepare o group red blood cells. the results showed that the optimal inducing conditions for alpha-galactosidase expression were iptg 0.1 mmol/l, 37 degrees c and 2 hours. the specific enzyme activity of purified protein increased from 0.42 u/mg to 2.1 u/mg as compared with pre-purification. and, the conditions of b to o blood group conversion were  26 degrees c, ph 6.8 (neutral ph condition) and 2 hours. moreover, 225 microg of  the enzyme could converse 1 ml b red blood cells to o completely. it is concluded that the technology of expression and purification of recombinant alpha-galactosidase has been established, and the purified protein can converse b red blood cells to o completely, which means that an effective enzyme conversing  b red blood cells to o has been obtained.
