TI  == comparison of rufloxacin and norfloxacin effects on faecal flora.
AB  == the suppression of faecal escherichia coli by quinolones was studied in a randomized cross-over phase i trial with single oral doses of 400 mg rufloxacin or norfloxacin. both drugs caused > 70% decontamination in a similar number of subjects in the 72 h post-dose period (83% vs 100% respectively), but suppression of e. coli at 168 h was significantly (p < 0.05) higher after rufloxacin (83.3 vs 40%).
