PMID== 8197037
TI  == bactericidal activity of low-dose ceftizoxime plus metronidazole compared with cefoxitin and ampicillin-sulbactam.
AB  == eighteen volunteers received ceftizoxime 1 g plus metronidazole 500 mg intravenously every 12 hours, cefoxitin 2 g intravenously every 6 hours, and ampicillin-sulbactam 3 g every 6 hours in a triple-crossover, open-label study to compare serum bactericidal titers (sbts) against two strains of escherichia coli  and bacteroides fragilis. serum was analyzed for drug concentration and bactericidal activity. ceftizoxime-metronidazole exhibited a significantly greater (p < 0.05) area under the bactericidal curve and percentage of the dosing interval with sbts of 1:2 or above against e. coli than cefoxitin or ampicillin-sulbactam. the respective values were equal to those of ampicillin-sulbactam for one strain of b. fragilis (both greater than cefoxitin)  and greater than cefoxitin and ampicillin-sulbactam for the other strain. a 1-g dose of ceftizoxime given with metronidazole 500 mg every 12 hours should be an effective alternative to standard antibiotic treatment of mixed aerobic-anaerobic bacterial infections.
