PMID== 1510410
TI  == biochemical characterization of the metallo-beta-lactamase ccra from bacteroides  fragilis tal3636.
AB  == the ccra beta-lactamase from bacteroides fragilis tal3636 was cloned into escherichia coli and purified from inclusion bodies. this group 3 metalloenzyme hydrolyzed most beta-lactam antibiotics, including cephamycins and carbapenems. following inhibition by chelators, enzyme activity was recovered with the cations zn2+ and co2+. clavulanate and sulbactam were activators; tazobactam at 10 microm inactivated the enzyme.
