PMID== 3182417
TI  == in-vitro and in-vivo activities of t-3262, a new pyridone carboxylic acid.
AB  == t-3262[p-toluenesulfonic acid salt of dl-7-(3-amino-1-pyrrolidinyl)-1-(2,4-difluorophenyl)-6-fluoro-1, 4-dihydro-4-oxo-1, 8-naphthyridine-3-carboxylic acid monohydrate] is a new pyridone carboxylic acid with a broad spectrum of antibacterial activity against  gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria. the activity of t-3262 against most enterobacteriaceae was comparable with that of ciprofloxacin except proteus spp.  and providencia rettgeri and exceeded that of ofloxacin and norfloxacin. the activity of t-3262 against pseudomonas aeruginosa was comparable with that of ciprofloxacin, and t-3262 was more active than the other new quinolones against acinetobacter calcoaceticus, branhamella catarrhalis and haemophilus influenzae,  and also against staphylococci, streptococci, and bacteroides fragilis. the protective effects of a single oral dose of t-3262 on systemic infection in mice  were greater than norfloxacin. t-3262 was as effective as ofloxacin and ciprofloxacin against systemic infections in an animal model with escherichia coli and klebsiella pneumoniae, and more active against ps. aeruginosa infections. t-3262 showed excellent activity against staphylococcal and streptococcal infections.
