PMID== 3112527
TI  == experimentally induced bacteroides infections in the rabbit.
AB  == rabbits were infected with bacteroides fragilis, b. macacae and b. gingivalis in  monoinfection, mixed bacteroides infection, and mixed infection of b. gingivalis  with streptococcus faecalis, escherichia coli and clostridium sporogenes. monoinfection gave rise to localised, nodular abscesses at cell levels greater than 0.5 x 10(5) cfu ml-1, the severity of which was dose related. mixed infections including b. gingivalis caused severe spreading lesions and affected organs distant from the injection site. histopathological studies indicate an inflammatory response with gas vacuolation and local necrosis.
TIHT== 
