PMID== 3516885
TI  == t-lymphocyte involvement in abscess formation in nonimmune mice.
AB  == athymic mice formed significantly smaller abscesses than euthymic mice in response to the intraperitoneal inoculation of an abscess-inducing mixture of escherichia coli, bacteroides fragilis, and autoclaved colonic contents, an abscess-potentiating agent. adoptive transfer of nonimmune, thy-1-positive spleen cells to athymic mice restored their ability to make abscesses of sizes similar to those in controls, indicating that t lymphocytes contribute to abscess formation in normal mice.
