PMID== 3928575
TI  == in-vitro and in-vivo activities of a novel cephamycin mt-141 against the bacteroides fragilis group in comparison with six cephem antibiotics.
AB  == mt-141 inhibited 90% of the clinical isolates of bacteroides fragilis at 3.13 mg/l, whereas six reference cephem antibiotics inhibited them at 12.5- greater than 100 mg/l. mt-141 was stable to the bacteroides beta-lactamases, but the stability alone could not explain the potent activity of mt-141 against the other bacteroides spp., which produced only small amounts of beta-lactamase, but were resistant to other cephem antibiotics. mt-141 exhibited a higher killing rate and more potent in-vivo efficacy than the reference cephem antibiotics against bact.  fragilis no. 36 combined with escherichia coli no. 29. in conclusion, the in-vitro and in-vivo anti-bacteroides activities of mt-141 ranked first among those of the cephem antibiotics compared.
