TI  == [in vitro and in vivo antimicrobial activities of cefmetazole against bacteroides fragilis].
AB  == cefmetazole was investigated on stability to beta-lactamases produced by bacteroides fragilis and on therapeutic effects in mice infected with b. fragilis. 1. cefmetazole, like other cephamycins, was found extremely stable to beta-lactamases obtained from b. fragilis. 2. cefmetazole showed good antimicrobial activities to 50 strains of b. fragilis and extremely high stability to their beta-lactamases. 3. cefmetazole showed an excellent protecting effect to infections due to beta-lactamase producing b. fragilis. 4. cefmetazole  exhibited an excellent chemotherapeutic effect against polymicrobial infections in mice due to e. coli (beta-lactamase -)and b. fragilis (beta-lactamase +).
